        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Kingston Jamaica</placeName> <date>Novr 29<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 5611</date>.</p>
			<p>To <addressee>Revd I Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Respected Friend</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">Your kind favor<lb/> accompanied by the Box containing the pair<lb/> of Lamps and Occidents came to hand for<lb/> the which I am greatly obliged. The contents<lb/> of your esteemed letter I regret to <sic>sa</sic> I cannot<lb/> at present fully answer being much fatigued<lb/> both mentally and bodily by illness in the fa&#45;<lb/>mily. To the dreadful state of the <placeName>Island</placeName><lb/> you are by this time no stranger.<lb/> My mind is too much disturbed to give the<lb/> due particulars several distant members of<lb/> our family have been attacked proving<lb/> fatal to a cousin and her husband. The others<lb/> are thank Heaven on the recovery.<lb/> How truly tis proven&#44; that there is &#34;good in evil.<lb/> How many hearts have turned to righteous&#45;<lb/>ness&#44; how many unmindful of their own<lb/> mortality have now discovered the mere<lb/> worm in themselves. I write not my friend as one<lb/> over Righteous&#44; far from it I know myself</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>convinced that the performance of some duties are<lb/> at times neglected&#44; and too often depend on the indul&#45;<lb/>gence of an All merciful Creator. Who knows<lb/> my heart and mind with the will to perform all<lb/> duties&#59; but however mindful we may be of all<lb/> this tis harrowing to see or hear of thousands<lb/> being summoned to the throne at one moments<lb/> notice. May He in His infinite mercy guard us all<lb/> and give us length of days for the full and faithful<lb/> execution of His will. I trust my friend that<lb/> my next will find me in spirits to give due<lb/> attention to your favor.</p>
			<p>The sales also came to hand in good condition.<lb/> Love to all friends and tell them they must not<lb/> be angry at my <sic>silense</sic> for the present.</p>
			<p>And now my kind friend that Heaven may<lb/> prosper your way and lead you out of the<lb/> many snares which have been laid for<lb/> you&#59; guiding you in your <add>&#63;</add> duty which<lb/> you have so faithfully nurtured and bring you<lb/> in the <add>&#63;</add> of hearts capable of appreciating<lb/> the true servant of the most High&#44; are<lb/> the wishes of your Friend and Pupil</p>
          <p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author"><hi rend="underline">Simha</hi> <hi rend="underline">C</hi> <hi rend="underline">Peixotto</hi></persName></p>
			<p>My dear Grandpa<add>&#63;</add> joins<lb/> me in all the <add>&#63;</add> wishes<lb/> and hopes you will stand your<lb/> ground. We have read the<lb/> <sic>defence</sic>&#59; and could add many<lb/> truths thereto from many years<lb/> personal observation.</p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p><addressee>Revd. I Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName><hi rend="underline">Philadelphia</hi></placeName></p>
			<p rend="This line is written in pencil"><placeName>Walnut St Number 13</placeName></p>
          
